| Strong Neg GEX | 49 | -1.13% | 57.1% | +1.97% | 57.1% | 85.7% |

### Counterintuitive: Negative GEX Has Higher Returns

| Metric | Pos GEX (N=1,876) | Neg GEX (N=175) | Delta |
|--------|-------------------|-----------------|-------|
| 5d avg return | +0.23% | +0.86% | -0.62% |
| 20d avg return | +0.95% | +3.11% | -2.17% |
| Fwd 5d vol | 13.3% | 35.4% | -22.1% |
| Tail event prob | 17.4% | 79.4% | -62.0% |

**Why?** Negative GEX = crash-then-rip. Higher avg returns because V-shaped bounces are massive, but eat -2.5% drawdowns. Positive GEX = smooth, steady gains with 60% less tail risk.

